<p class="">I am sure that the right hon. Gentleman is being unwittingly ungenerous and inaccurate in respect of my right hon. Friend, who did not say that it was impossible. He said that they were very closely integrated, and that to do what was suggested would mean a diversification of essential and skilled labour and time which the country could not afford. As to the right hon. Gentleman's second point, if he had taken some other good advice from our "speakers' notes" in 1945 he would not be in the miserable mess in which he is now.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
